abstract: Afghan leaders sent combat forces to capture a belligerent warlord, but many critics believed the deadly raid was a political stunt gone awry.
snippet: Afghan leaders sent combat forces to capture a belligerent warlord, but many critics believed the deadly raid was a political stunt gone awry.
lead_paragraph: MAZAR-I-SHARIF, Afghanistan — For nearly 24 hours, the center of Mazar-i-Sharif, one of Afghanistan’s economic hubs, became a front line for a battle that included machine guns, rocket-propelled grenades and helicopter gunships. And it didn’t even involve the Taliban.

abstract: Britain's government is set to announce its choice for the next boss of the Bank of England, one of its most pressing decisions after last week's election victory of Prime Minister Boris Johnson.
snippet: Britain's government is set to announce its choice for the next boss of the Bank of England, one of its most pressing decisions after last week's election victory of Prime Minister Boris Johnson.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain's government is set to announce its choice for the next boss of the Bank of England, one of its most pressing decisions after last week's election victory of Prime Minister Boris Johnson.

headline_print_headline: Britain Set to Announce Next Bank of England Governor

abstract: Supporters of Lebanon's two main Shiite groups Hezbollah and Amal clashed with security forces and set fires to cars in the capital early Tuesday, apparently angered by a video circulating online that showed a man insulting Shiite figures.
snippet: Supporters of Lebanon's two main Shiite groups Hezbollah and Amal clashed with security forces and set fires to cars in the capital early Tuesday, apparently angered by a video circulating online that showed a man insulting Shiite figures.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Supporters of Lebanon's two main Shiite groups Hezbollah and Amal clashed with security forces and set fires to cars in the capital early Tuesday, apparently angered by a video circulating online that showed a man insulting Shiite figures.
headline_main: 3rd Night of Clashes as Lebanon Puts Off Talks on New PM
headline_print_headline: 3rd Night of Clashes as Lebanon Puts Off Talks on New PM

abstract: European shares hit record highs on Monday, rising for the fourth successive session as a preliminary U.S.-China trade deal helped extend a rally sparked by the British Conservative Party's election victory.
snippet: European shares hit record highs on Monday, rising for the fourth successive session as a preliminary U.S.-China trade deal helped extend a rally sparked by the British Conservative Party's election victory.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - European shares hit record highs on Monday, rising for the fourth successive session as a preliminary U.S.-China trade deal helped extend a rally sparked by the British Conservative Party's election victory.
headline_main: European Shares Touch All-Time High as Trade, Brexit Fog Clears
headline_print_headline: European Shares Touch All-Time High as Trade, Brexit Fog Clears

abstract: British shares continued to power higher on Monday as a preliminary U.S.-China trade deal and hopes of an orderly Brexit after UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson's election victory saw investors flock to perceived riskier assets, such as equities.
snippet: British shares continued to power higher on Monday as a preliminary U.S.-China trade deal and hopes of an orderly Brexit after UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson's election victory saw investors flock to perceived riskier assets, such as equities.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - British shares continued to power higher on Monday as a preliminary U.S.-China trade deal and hopes of an orderly Brexit after UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson's election victory saw investors flock to perceived riskier assets, such as equities.
headline_main: China-U.S. Trade Deal, Brexit Hopes Turbo Charge UK Stocks
headline_print_headline: China-U.S. Trade Deal, Brexit Hopes Turbo Charge UK Stocks

abstract: The nomination of Lebanon's next prime minister was postponed on Monday as new complications surfaced in efforts to agree a government that is urgently needed to pull the country out of a destabilising economic crisis.
snippet: The nomination of Lebanon's next prime minister was postponed on Monday as new complications surfaced in efforts to agree a government that is urgently needed to pull the country out of a destabilising economic crisis.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — The nomination of Lebanon's next prime minister was postponed on Monday as new complications surfaced in efforts to agree a government that is urgently needed to pull the country out of a destabilising economic crisis.
headline_main: Lebanon Delays PM Designation as Political Crisis Deepens
headline_print_headline: Lebanon Delays PM Designation as Political Crisis Deepens

abstract: China’s president endorses Hong Kong’s embattled leader, Carrie Lam, despite the rout of her political allies in local elections three weeks ago.
snippet: China’s president endorses Hong Kong’s embattled leader, Carrie Lam, despite the rout of her political allies in local elections three weeks ago.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China’s top leader backed Chief Executive Carrie Lam of Hong Kong on Monday despite the monthslong protests that have rocked the city and the recent landslide defeat in local elections of political parties aligned with her.

abstract: A groundbreaking legislative session has hit pause, with a slew of legislation awaiting Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo’s signature or veto.
snippet: A groundbreaking legislative session has hit pause, with a slew of legislation awaiting Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo’s signature or veto.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY, N.Y. — For six months, Democrats in the State Capitol flexed the power of unbridled one-party rule, ushering in a sweeping overhaul of New York’s housing, environmental, criminal and social justice laws.

abstract: Several people have been killed as unrest spreads to new corners of the country. Many see the passage of a new law as anti-Muslim.
snippet: Several people have been killed as unrest spreads to new corners of the country. Many see the passage of a new law as anti-Muslim.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s government has rounded up thousands of Muslims in Kashmir, revoked the area’s autonomy and enforced a citizenship test in northeastern India that left nearly two million people potentially stateless, many of them Muslim.
